text=(:nogroupheader:)%0a(:Summary::)%0a(:Published::)%0a(:Author:[[~GiverofMemory]]:)%0a(:License:[[https://en.m.wikipedia.org/wiki/Res_communis|Site License]]:)%0a(:Update::)%0a(:Maintainer:[[~GiverofMemory]]:)%0a(:Creator:[[]]:)%0a(:Categories:[[!]]:)%0a(:Also:none:)%0a(:Archive:[[|Archive.is]], [[|Archive.org]]:)%0a(:Download:[[{$FullName}?action=print|URL]],[[https://www.web2pdfconvert.com/|PDF from URL]]:)%0a%0aThe Gospel of Thomas%0aby Mark M. Mattison%0aThe following translation has been committed to the public domain and may be freely copied and used, changed or unchanged, for any purpose. It is based on the Coptic text of Nag Hammadi Codex II, 2. For information about the surviving manuscripts of the Gospel of Thomas, see the Manuscript Information page. For additional information about the translation, see the introduction to the PDF version.%0a%0aFor some reflections on the potential meaning and significance of Thomas' Gospel for us today, see my book, The Gospel of Thomas: A New Translation for Spiritual Seekers. Note that Luminescence, L.L.C. earns commissions for purchases made through links in this post.%0a%0aSymbols%0a[ ] Gap in the text%0a( ) Editorial insertion%0a/ \ Editorial correction of a scribal error%0a%0a%0aPrologue%0a%0aThese are the hidden sayings that the living Jesus spoke and Didymos Judas Thomas wrote down.%0a%0a %0a%0aSaying 1: True Meaning%0a%0aAnd he said, "Whoever discovers the meaning of these sayings won't taste death."%0a%0a %0a%0aSaying 2: Seek and Find%0a%0aJesus said, "Whoever seeks shouldn't stop until they find. When they find, they'll be disturbed. When they're disturbed, they'll be [â€¦] amazed, and reign over the All."%0a%0a %0a%0aSaying 3: Seeking Within%0a%0aJesus said, "If your leaders tell you, 'Look, the kingdom is in heaven,' then the birds of heaven will precede you. If they tell you, 'It's in the sea,' then the fish will precede you. Rather, the kingdom is within you and outside of you.%0a%0a"When you know yourselves, then you'll be known, and you'll realize that you're the children of the living Father. But if you don't know yourselves, then you live in poverty, and you are the poverty."%0a%0a %0a%0aSaying 4: First and Last%0a%0aJesus said, "The older person won't hesitate to ask a little seven-day-old child about the place of life, and they'll live, because many who are first will be last, and they'll become one."%0a%0a %0a%0aSaying 5: Hidden and Revealed%0a%0aJesus said, "Know what's in front of your face, and what's hidden from you will be revealed to you, because there's nothing hidden that won't be revealed."%0a%0a %0a%0aSaying 6: Public Ritual%0a%0aHis disciples said to him, "Do you want us to fast? And how should we pray? Should we make donations? And what food should we avoid?"%0a%0aJesus said, "Don't lie, and don't do what you hate, because everything is revealed in the sight of heaven; for there's nothing hidden that won't be revealed, and nothing covered up that will stay secret."%0a%0a %0a%0aSaying 7: The Lion and the Human%0a%0aJesus said, "Blessed is the lion that's eaten by a human and then becomes human, but how awful for the human who's eaten by a lion, and the lion becomes human."%0a%0a %0a%0aSaying 8: The Parable of the Fish%0a%0aHe said, "The human being is like a wise fisher who cast a net into the sea and drew it up from the sea full of little fish. Among them the wise fisher found a fine large fish and cast all the little fish back down into the sea, easily choosing the large fish. Anyone who has ears to hear should hear!"%0a%0a %0a%0aSaying 9: The Parable of the Sower%0a%0aJesus said, "Look, a sower went out, took a handful of seeds, and scattered them. Some fell on the roadside; the birds came and gathered them. Others fell on the rock; they didn't take root in the soil and ears of grain didn't rise toward heaven. Yet others fell on thorns; they choked the seeds and worms ate them. Finally, others fell on good soil; it produced fruit up toward heaven, some sixty times as much and some a hundred and twenty."%0a%0a %0a%0aSaying 10: Jesus and Fire (1)%0a%0aJesus said, "I've cast fire on the world, and look, I'm watching over it until it blazes."%0a%0a %0a%0aSaying 11: Those Who Are Living Won't Die (1)%0a%0aJesus said, "This heaven will disappear, and the one above it will disappear too. Those who are dead aren't alive, and those who are living won't die. In the days when you ate what was dead, you made it alive. When you're in the light, what will you do? On the day when you were one, you became divided. But when you become divided, what will you do?"%0a%0a %0a%0aSaying 12: James the Just%0a%0aThe disciples said to Jesus, "We know you're going to leave us. Who will lead us then?"%0a%0aJesus said to them, "Wherever you are, you'll go to James the Just, for whom heaven and earth came into being."%0a%0a %0a%0aSaying 13: Thomas' Confession%0a%0aJesus said to his disciples, "If you were to compare me to someone, who would you say I'm like?"%0a%0aSimon Peter said to him, "You're like a just angel."%0a%0aMatthew said to him, "You're like a wise philosopher."%0a%0aThomas said to him, "Teacher, I'm completely unable to say whom you're like."%0a%0aJesus said, "I'm not your teacher. Because you've drunk, you've become intoxicated by the bubbling spring I've measured out."%0a%0aHe took him aside and told him three things. When Thomas returned to his companions, they asked, "What did Jesus say to you?"%0a%0aThomas said to them, "If I tell you one of the things he said to me, you'll pick up stones and cast them at me, and fire will come out of the stones and burn you up."%0a%0a %0a%0aSaying 14: Public Ministry%0a%0aJesus said to them, "If you fast, you'll bring guilt upon yourselves; and if you pray, you'll be condemned; and if you make donations, you'll harm your spirits.%0a%0a"If they welcome you when you enter any land and go around in the countryside, heal those who are sick among them and eat whatever they give you, because it's not what goes into your mouth that will defile you. What comes out of your mouth is what will defile you."%0a%0a %0a%0aSaying 15: Worship%0a%0aJesus said, "When you see the one who wasn't born of a woman, fall down on your face and worship that person. That's your Father."%0a%0a %0a%0aSaying 16: Not Peace, but War%0a%0aJesus said, "Maybe people think that I've come to cast peace on the world, and they don't know that I've come to cast divisions on the earth: fire, sword, and war. Where there are five in a house, there'll be three against two and two against three, father against and son and son against father. They'll stand up and be one."%0a%0a %0a%0aSaying 17: Divine Gift%0a%0aJesus said, "I'll give you what no eye has ever seen, no ear has ever heard, no hand has ever touched, and no human mind has ever thought."%0a%0a %0a%0aSaying 18: Beginning and End%0a%0aThe disciples said to Jesus, "Tell us about our end. How will it come?"%0a%0aJesus said, "Have you discovered the beginning so that you can look for the end? Because the end will be where the beginning is. Blessed is the one who will stand up in the beginning. They'll know the end, and won't taste death."%0a%0a %0a%0aSaying 19: Five Trees in Paradise%0a%0aJesus said, "Blessed is the one who came into being before coming into being. If you become my disciples and listen to my message, these stones will become your servants; because there are five trees in paradise which don't change in summer or winter, and their leaves don't fall. Whoever knows them won't taste death."%0a%0a %0a%0aSaying 20: The Parable of the Mustard Seed%0a%0aThe disciples asked Jesus, "Tell us, what can the kingdom of heaven be compared to?"%0a%0aHe said to them, "It can be compared to a mustard seed. Though it's the smallest of all the seeds, when it falls on tilled soil it makes a plant so large that it shelters the birds of heaven."%0a%0a %0a%0aSaying 21: The Parables of the Field, the Bandits, and the Reaper%0a%0aMary said to Jesus, "Whom are your disciples like?"%0a%0aHe said, "They're like little children living in a field which isn't theirs. When the owners of the field come, they'll say, 'Give our field back to us.' They'll strip naked in front of them to let them have it and give them their field.%0a%0a"So I say that if the owner of the house realizes the bandit is coming, they'll watch out beforehand and won't let the bandit break into the house of their domain and steal their possessions. You, then, watch out for the world! Prepare to defend yourself so that the bandits don't attack you, because what you're expecting will come. May there be a wise person among you!%0a%0a"When the fruit ripened, the reaper came quickly, sickle in hand, and harvested it. Anyone who has ears to hear should hear!"%0a%0a %0a%0aSaying 22: Making the Two into One%0a%0aJesus saw some little children nursing. He said to his disciples, "These nursing children can be compared to those who enter the kingdom."%0a%0aThey said to him, "Then we'll enter the kingdom as little children?"%0a%0aJesus said to them, "When you make the two into one, and make the inner like the outer and the outer like the inner, and the upper like the lower, and so make the male and the female a single one so that the male won't be male nor the female female; when you make eyes in the place of an eye, a hand in the place of a hand, a foot in the place of a foot, and an image in the place of an image; then you'll enter [the kingdom]."%0a%0a %0a%0aSaying 23: Those Who are Chosen (1)%0a%0aJesus said, "I'll choose you, one out of a thousand and two out of ten thousand, and they'll stand as a single one."%0a%0a %0a%0aSaying 24: Light%0a%0aHis disciples said, "Show us the place where you are, because we need to look for it."%0a%0aHe said to them, "Anyone who has ears to hear should hear! Light exists within a person of light, and they light up the whole world. If they don't shine, there's darkness."%0a%0a %0a%0aSaying 25: Love and Protect%0a%0aJesus said, "Love your brother as your own soul. Protect them like the pupil of your eye."%0a%0a %0a%0aSaying 26: Speck and Beam%0a%0aJesus said, "You see the speck that's in your brother's eye, but you don't see the beam in your own eye. When you get the beam out of your own eye, then you'll be able to see clearly to get the speck out of your brother's eye."%0a%0a %0a%0aSaying 27: Fasting and Sabbath%0a%0a"If you don't fast from the world, you won't find the kingdom. If you don't make the Sabbath into a Sabbath, you won't see the Father."%0a%0a %0a%0aSaying 28: The World is Drunk%0a%0aJesus said, "I stood in the middle of the world and appeared to them in the flesh. I found them all drunk; I didn't find any of them thirsty. My soul ached for the children of humanity, because they were blind in their hearts and couldn't see. They came into the world empty and plan on leaving the world empty. Meanwhile, they're drunk. When they shake off their wine, then they'll change."%0a%0a %0a%0aSaying 29: Spirit and Body%0a%0aJesus said, "If the flesh came into existence because of spirit, that's amazing. If spirit came into existence because of the body, that's really amazing! But I'm amazed at how [such] great wealth has been placed in this poverty."%0a%0a %0a%0aSaying 30: Divine Presence%0a%0aJesus said, "Where there are three deities, they're divine. Where there are two or one, I'm with them."%0a%0a %0a%0aSaying 31: Prophet and Doctor%0a%0aJesus said, "No prophet is welcome in their own village. No doctor heals those who know them."%0a%0a %0a%0aSaying 32: The Parable of the Fortified City%0a%0aJesus said, "A city built and fortified on a high mountain can't fall, nor can it be hidden."%0a%0a %0a%0aSaying 33: The Parable of the Lamp%0a%0aJesus said, "What you hear with one ear, listen to with both, then proclaim from your rooftops. No one lights a lamp and puts it under a basket or in a hidden place. Rather, they put it on the stand so that everyone who comes and goes can see its light."%0a%0a %0a%0aSaying 34: The Parable of Those Who Can't See%0a%0aJesus said, "If someone who's blind leads someone else who's blind, both of them fall into a pit."%0a%0a %0a%0aSaying 35: The Parable of Binding the Strong%0a%0aJesus said, "No one can break into the house of the strong and take it by force without tying the hands of the strong. Then they can loot the house."%0a%0a %0a%0aSaying 36: Anxiety%0a%0aJesus said, "Don't be anxious from morning to evening or from evening to morning about what you'll wear."%0a%0a %0a%0aSaying 37: Seeing Jesus%0a%0aHis disciples said, "When will you appear to us? When will we see you?"%0a%0aJesus said, "When you strip naked without being ashamed, and throw your clothes on the ground and stomp on them as little children would, then [you'll] see the Son of the Living One and won't be afraid."%0a%0a %0a%0aSaying 38: Finding Jesus%0a%0aJesus said, "Often you've wanted to hear this message that I'm telling you, and you don't have anyone else from whom to hear it. There will be days when you'll look for me, but you won't be able to find me."%0a%0a %0a%0aSaying 39: The Keys of Knowledge%0a%0aJesus said, "The Pharisees and the scholars have taken the keys of knowledge and hidden them. They haven't entered, and haven't let others enter who wanted to. So be wise as serpents and innocent as doves."%0a%0a %0a%0aSaying 40: A Grapevine%0a%0aJesus said, "A grapevine has been planted outside of the Father. Since it's malnourished, it'll be pulled up by its root and destroyed."%0a%0a %0a%0aSaying 41: More and Less%0a%0aJesus said, "Whoever has something in hand will be given more, but whoever doesn't have anything will lose even what little they do have."%0a%0a %0a%0aSaying 42: Passing By%0a%0aJesus said, "Become passersby."%0a%0a %0a%0aSaying 43: The Tree and the Fruit%0a%0aHis disciples said to him, "Who are you to say these things to us?"%0a%0a"You don't realize who I am from what I say to you, but you've become like those Judeans who either love the tree but hate its fruit, or love the fruit but hate the tree."%0a%0a %0a%0aSaying 44: Blasphemy%0a%0aJesus said, "Whoever blasphemes the Father will be forgiven, and whoever blasphemes the Son will be forgiven, but whoever blasphemes the Holy Spirit will not be forgiven, neither on earth nor in heaven."%0a%0a %0a%0aSaying 45: Good and Evil%0a%0aJesus said, "Grapes aren't harvested from thorns, nor are figs gathered from thistles, because they don't produce fruit. [A person who's good] brings good things out of their treasure, and a person who's [evil] brings evil things out of their evil treasure. They say evil things because their heart is full of evil."%0a%0a %0a%0aSaying 46: Greater than John the Baptizer%0a%0aJesus said, "From Adam to John the Baptizer, no one's been born who's so much greater than John the Baptizer that they shouldn't avert their eyes. But I say that whoever among you will become a little child will know the kingdom and become greater than John."%0a%0a %0a%0aSaying 47: The Parables of Divided Loyalties,%0aNew Wine in Old Wineskins, and New Patch on Old Cloth%0a%0aJesus said, "It's not possible for anyone to mount two horses or stretch two bows, and it's not possible for a servant to follow two leaders, because they'll respect one and despise the other.%0a%0a"No one drinks old wine and immediately wants to drink new wine. And new wine isn't put in old wineskins, because they'd burst. Nor is old wine put in new wineskins, because it'd spoil.%0a%0a"A new patch of cloth isn't sewn onto an old coat, because it'd tear apart."%0a%0a %0a%0aSaying 48: Unity (1)%0a%0aJesus said, "If two make peace with each other in a single house, they'll say to the mountain, 'Go away,' and it will."%0a%0a %0a%0aSaying 49: Those Who Are Chosen (2)%0a%0aJesus said, "Blessed are those who are one â€“ those who are chosen, because you'll find the kingdom. You've come from there and will return there."%0a%0a %0a%0aSaying 50: Our Origin and Identity%0a%0aJesus said, "If they ask you, 'Where do you come from?' tell them, 'We've come from the light, the place where light came into being by itself, [established] itself, and appeared in their image.'%0a%0a"If they ask you, 'Is it you?' then say, 'We are its children, and we're chosen by our living Father.'%0a%0a"If they ask you, 'What's the sign of your Father in you?' then say, 'It's movement and rest.'"%0a%0a %0a%0aSaying 51: The New World%0a%0aHis disciples said to him, "When will the dead have rest, and when will the new world come?"%0a%0aHe said to them, "What you're looking for has already come, but you don't know it."%0a%0a %0a%0aSaying 52: Twenty-Four Prophets%0a%0aHis disciples said to him, "Twenty-four prophets have spoken in Israel, and they all spoke of you."%0a%0aHe said to them, "You've ignored the Living One right in front of you, and you've talked about those who are dead."%0a%0a %0a%0aSaying 53: True Circumcision%0a%0aHis disciples said to him, "Is circumcision useful, or not?"%0a%0aHe said to them, "If it were useful, parents would have children who are born circumcised. But the true circumcision in spirit has become profitable in every way."%0a%0a %0a%0aSaying 54: Those Who Are Poor%0a%0aJesus said, "Blessed are those who are poor, for yours is the kingdom of heaven."%0a%0a %0a%0aSaying 55: Discipleship (1)%0a%0aJesus said, "Whoever doesn't hate their father and mother can't become my disciple, and whoever doesn't hate their brothers and sisters and take up their cross like I do isn't worthy of me."%0a%0a %0a%0aSaying 56: The World is a Corpse%0a%0aJesus said, "Whoever has known the world has found a corpse. Whoever has found a corpse, of them the world isn't worthy."%0a%0a %0a%0aSaying 57: The Parable of the Weeds%0a%0aJesus said, "My Fathers' kingdom can be compared to someone who had [good] seed. Their enemy came by night and sowed weeds among the good seed. The person didn't let anyone pull out the weeds, 'so that you don't pull out the wheat along with the weeds,' they said to them. 'On the day of the harvest, the weeds will be obvious. Then they'll be pulled out and burned.'"%0a%0a %0a%0aSaying 58: Finding Life%0a%0aJesus said, "Blessed is the person who's gone to a lot of trouble. They've found life."%0a%0a %0a%0aSaying 59: The Living One%0a%0aJesus said, "Look for the Living One while you're still alive. If you die and then try to look for him, you won't be able to."%0a%0a %0a%0aSaying 60: Don't Become a Corpse%0a%0aThey saw a Samaritan carrying a lamb to Judea. He said to his disciples, "What do you think he's going to do with that lamb?"%0a%0aThey said to him, "He's going to kill it and eat it."%0a%0aHe said to them, "While it's living, he won't eat it, but only after he kills it and it becomes a corpse."%0a%0aThey said, "He can't do it any other way."%0a%0aHe said to them, "You, too, look for a resting place, so that you won't become a corpse and be eaten."%0a%0a %0a%0aSaying 61: Jesus and Salome%0a%0aJesus said, "Two will rest on a couch. One will die, the other will live."%0a%0aSalome said, "Who are you, Sir, to climb onto my couch and eat off my table as if you're from someone?"%0a%0aJesus said to her, "I'm the one who exists in equality. Some of what belongs to my Father was given to me."%0a%0a"I'm your disciple."%0a%0a"So I'm telling you, if someone is /equal\, they'll be full of light; but if they're divided, they'll be full of darkness."%0a%0a %0a%0aSaying 62: Mysteries%0a%0aJesus said, "I tell my mysteries to [those who are worthy of my] mysteries. Don't let your left hand know what your right hand is doing."%0a%0a %0a%0aSaying 63: The Parable of the Rich Fool%0a%0aJesus said, "There was a rich man who had much money. He said, 'I'll use my money to sow, reap, plant, and fill my barns with fruit, so that I won't need anything.' That's what he was thinking to himself, but he died that very night. Anyone who has ears to hear should hear!"%0a%0a %0a%0aSaying 64: The Parable of the Dinner Party%0a%0aJesus said, "Someone was planning on having guests. When dinner was ready, they sent their servant to call the visitors.%0a%0a"The servant went to the first and said, 'My master invites you.'%0a%0a"They said, 'Some merchants owe me money. They're coming tonight. I need to go and give them instructions. Excuse me from the dinner.'%0a%0a"The servant went to another one and said, 'My master invites you.'%0a%0a"They said, "I've just bought a house and am needed for the day. I won't have time.'%0a%0a"The servant went to another one and said, 'My master invites you.'%0a%0a"They said, 'My friend is getting married and I'm going to make dinner. I can't come. Excuse me from the dinner.'%0a%0a"The servant went to another one and said, 'My master invites you.'%0a%0a"They said, "I've just bought a farm and am going to collect the rent. I can't come. Excuse me.'%0a%0a"The servant went back and told the master, 'The ones you've invited to the dinner have excused themselves.'%0a%0a"The master said to their servant, 'Go out to the roads and bring whomever you find so that they can have dinner.'%0a%0a"Buyers and merchants won't [enter] the places of my Father."%0a%0a %0a%0aSaying 65: The Parable of the Sharecroppers%0a%0aHe said, "A [creditor] owned a vineyard. He leased it out to some sharecroppers to work it so he could collect its fruit.%0a%0a"He sent his servant so that the sharecroppers could give him the fruit of the vineyard. They seized his servant, beat him, and nearly killed him.%0a%0a"The servant went back and told his master. His master said, 'Maybe he just didn't know them.' He sent another servant, but the tenants beat that one too.%0a%0a"Then the master sent his son, thinking, 'Maybe they'll show some respect to my son.'%0a%0a"Because they knew that he was the heir of the vineyard, the sharecroppers seized and killed him. Anyone who has ears to hear should hear!"%0a%0a %0a%0aSaying 66: The Rejected Cornerstone%0a%0aJesus said, "Show me the stone the builders rejected; that's the cornerstone."%0a%0a %0a%0aSaying 67: Knowing Isn't Everything%0a%0aJesus said, "Whoever knows everything, but is personally lacking, lacks everything."%0a%0a %0a%0aSaying 68: Persecution%0a%0aJesus said, "Blessed are you when you're hated and persecuted, and no place will be found where you've been persecuted."%0a%0a %0a%0aSaying 69: Those Who Are Persecuted%0a%0aJesus said, "Blessed are those who've been persecuted in their own hearts. They've truly known the Father. Blessed are those who are hungry, so that their stomachs may be filled."%0a%0a %0a%0aSaying 70: Salvation is Within%0a%0aJesus said, "If you give birth to what's within you, what you have within you will save you. If you don't have that within [you], what you don't have within you [will] kill you."%0a%0a %0a%0aSaying 71: Destroying the Temple%0a%0aJesus said, "I'll destroy [this] house, and no one will be able to build it [â€¦]"%0a%0a %0a%0aSaying 72: Not a Divider%0a%0a[Someone said to him], "Tell my brothers to divide our inheritance with me."%0a%0aHe said to him, "Who made me a divider?"%0a%0aHe turned to his disciples and said to them, "Am I really a divider?"%0a%0a %0a%0aSaying 73: Workers for the Harvest%0a%0aJesus said, "The harvest really is plentiful, but the workers are few. So pray that the Lord will send workers to the harvest."%0a%0a %0a%0aSaying 74: The Empty Well%0a%0aHe said, "Lord, many are gathered around the well, but there's nothing to drink."%0a%0a %0a%0aSaying 75: The Bridal Chamber%0a%0aJesus said, "Many are waiting at the door, but those who are one will enter the bridal chamber."%0a%0a %0a%0aSaying 76: The Parable of the Pearl%0a%0aJesus said, "The Father's kingdom can be compared to a merchant with merchandise who found a pearl. The merchant was wise; they sold their merchandise and bought that single pearl for themselves.%0a%0a"You, too, look for the treasure that doesn't perish but endures, where no moths come to eat and no worms destroy."%0a%0a %0a%0aSaying 77: Jesus is the All%0a%0aJesus said, "I'm the light that's over all. I am the All. The All has come from me and unfolds toward me.%0a%0a"Split a log; I'm there. Lift the stone, and you'll find me there."%0a%0a %0a%0aSaying 78: Into the Desert%0a%0aJesus said, "What did you go out into the desert to see? A reed shaken by the wind? A [person] wearing fancy clothes, [like your] rulers and powerful people? They (wear) fancy [clothes], but can't know the truth."%0a%0a %0a%0aSaying 79: Listening to the Message%0a%0aA woman in the crowd said to him, "Blessed is the womb that bore you, and the breasts that nourished you."%0a%0aHe said to [her], "Blessed are those who have listened to the message of the Father and kept it, because there will be days when you'll say, 'Blessed is the womb that didn't conceive and the breasts that haven't given milk.'"%0a%0a %0a%0aSaying 80: The World is a Body%0a%0aJesus said, "Whoever has known the world has found the body; but whoever has found the body, of them the world isn't worthy."%0a%0a %0a%0aSaying 81: Riches and Renunciation (1)%0a%0aJesus said, "Whoever has become rich should become a ruler, and whoever has power should renounce it."%0a%0a %0a%0aSaying 82: Jesus and Fire (2)%0a%0aJesus said, "Whoever is near me is near the fire, and whoever is far from me is far from the kingdom."%0a%0a %0a%0aSaying 83: Light and Images%0a%0aJesus said, "Images are revealed to people, but the light within them is hidden in the image of the Father's light. He'll be revealed, but his image will be hidden by his light."%0a%0a %0a%0aSaying 84: Our Previous Images%0a%0aJesus said, "When you see your likeness, you rejoice. But when you see your images that came into being before you did â€“ which don't die, and aren't revealed â€“ how much you'll have to bear!"%0a%0a %0a%0aSaying 85: Adam Wasn't Worthy%0a%0aJesus said, "Adam came into being from a great power and great wealth, but he didn't become worthy of you. If he had been worthy, [he wouldn't have tasted] death."%0a%0a %0a%0aSaying 86: Foxes and Birds%0a%0aJesus said, "[The foxes have dens] and the birds have nests, but the Son of Humanity has nowhere to lay his head and rest."%0a%0a %0a%0aSaying 87: Body and Soul%0a%0aJesus said, "How miserable is the body that depends on a body, and how miserable is the soul that depends on both."%0a%0a %0a%0aSaying 88: Angels and Prophets%0a%0aJesus said, "The angels and the prophets will come to you and give you what belongs to you. You'll give them what you have and ask yourselves, 'When will they come and take what is theirs?'"%0a%0a %0a%0aSaying 89: Inside and Outside%0a%0aJesus said, "Why do you wash the outside of the cup? Don't you know that whoever created the inside created the outside too?"%0a%0a %0a%0aSaying 90: Jesus' Yoke is Easy%0a%0aJesus said, "Come to me, because my yoke is easy and my requirements are light. You'll be refreshed."%0a%0a %0a%0aSaying 91: Reading the Signs%0a%0aThey said to him, "Tell us who you are so that we may trust you."%0a%0aHe said to them, "You read the face of the sky and the earth, but you don't know the one right in front of you, and you don't know how to read the present moment."%0a%0a %0a%0aSaying 92: Look and Find%0a%0aJesus said, "Look and you'll find. I didn't answer your questions before. Now I want to give you answers, but you aren't looking for them."%0a%0a %0a%0aSaying 93: Don't Throw Pearls to Pigs%0a%0a"Don't give what's holy to the dogs, or else it might be thrown on the manure pile. Don't throw pearls to the pigs, or else they might [â€¦]"%0a%0a %0a%0aSaying 94: Knock and It Will Be Opened%0a%0aJesus [said], "Whoever looks will find, [and whoever knocks], it will be opened for them."%0a%0a %0a%0aSaying 95: Giving Money%0a%0a[Jesus said], "If you have money, don't lend it at interest. Instead, give [it to] someone from whom you won't get it back."%0a%0a %0a%0aSaying 96: The Parable of the Yeast%0a%0aJesus [said], "The Father's kingdom can be compared to a woman who took a little yeast and [hid] it in flour. She made it into large loaves of bread. Anyone who has ears to hear should hear!"%0a%0a %0a%0aSaying 97: The Parable of the Jar of Flour%0a%0aJesus said, "The Father's kingdom can be compared to a woman carrying a jar of flour. While she was walking down [a] long road, the jar's handle broke and the flour spilled out behind her on the road. She didn't know it, and didn't realize there was a problem until she got home, put down the jar, and found it empty."%0a%0a %0a%0aSaying 98: The Parable of the Assassin%0a%0aJesus said, "The Father's kingdom can be compared to a man who wanted to kill someone powerful. He drew his sword in his house and drove it into the wall to figure out whether his hand was strong enough. Then he killed the powerful one."%0a%0a %0a%0aSaying 99: Jesus' True Family%0a%0aThe disciples said to him, "Your brothers and mother are standing outside."%0a%0aHe said to them, "The people here who do the will of my Father are my brothers and mother; they're the ones who will enter my Father's kingdom."%0a%0a %0a%0aSaying 100: Give to Caesar What Belongs to Caesar%0a%0aThey showed Jesus a gold coin and said to him, "Those who belong to Caesar demand tribute from us."%0a%0aHe said to them, "Give to Caesar what belongs to Caesar, give to God what belongs to God, and give to me what belongs to me."%0a%0a %0a%0aSaying 101: Discipleship (2)%0a%0a"Whoever doesn't hate their [father] and mother as I do can't become my [disciple], and whoever [doesn't] love their [father] and mother as I do can't become my [disciple]. For my mother [â€¦], but [my] true [Mother] gave me Life."%0a%0a %0a%0aSaying 102: The Dog in the Feeding Trough%0a%0aJesus said, "How awful for the Pharisees who are like a dog sleeping in a feeding trough for cattle, because the dog doesn't eat, and [doesn't let] the cattle eat either."%0a%0a %0a%0aSaying 103: The Parable of the Bandits%0a%0aJesus said, "Blessed is the one who knows where the bandits are going to enter. [They can] get up to assemble their defenses and be prepared to defend themselves before they arrive."%0a%0a %0a%0aSaying 104: Prayer and Fasting%0a%0aThey said to [Jesus], "Come, let's pray and fast today."%0a%0aJesus said, "What have I done wrong? Have I failed?%0a%0a"Rather, when the groom leaves the bridal chamber, then people should fast and pray."%0a%0a %0a%0aSaying 105: Knowing Father and Mother%0a%0aJesus said, "Whoever knows their father and mother will be called a bastard."%0a%0a %0a%0aSaying 106: Unity (2)%0a%0aJesus said, "When you make the two into one, you'll become Children of Humanity, and if you say 'Mountain, go away!', it'll go."%0a%0a %0a%0aSaying 107: The Parable of the Lost Sheep%0a%0aJesus said, "The kingdom can be compared to a shepherd who had a hundred sheep. The largest one strayed. He left the ninety-nine and looked for that one until he found it. Having gone through the trouble, he said to the sheep: 'I love you more than the ninety-nine.'"%0a%0a %0a%0aSaying 108: Becoming Like Jesus%0a%0aJesus said, "Whoever drinks from my mouth will become like me, and I myself will become like them; then, what's hidden will be revealed to them."%0a%0a %0a%0aSaying 109: The Parable of the Hidden Treasure%0a%0aJesus said, "The kingdom can be compared to someone who had a treasure [hidden] in their field. [They] didn't know about it. After they died, they left it to their son. The son didn't know it either. He took the field and sold it.%0a%0a"The buyer plowed the field, [found] the treasure, and began to loan money at interest to whomever they wanted."%0a%0a %0a%0aSaying 110: Riches and Renunciation (2)%0a%0aJesus said, "Whoever has found the world and become rich should renounce the world."%0a%0a %0a%0aSaying 111: Those Who are Living Won't Die (2)%0a%0aJesus said, "The heavens and the earth will roll up in front of you, and whoever lives from the Living One won't see death."%0a%0aDoesn't Jesus say, "Whoever finds themselves, of them the world isn't worthy"?%0a%0a %0a%0aSaying 112: Flesh and Soul%0a%0aJesus said, "How awful for the flesh that depends on the soul. How awful for the soul that depends on the flesh."%0a%0a %0a%0aSaying 113: The Kingdom is Already Present%0a%0aHis disciples said to him, "When will the kingdom come?"%0a%0a"It won't come by looking for it. They won't say, 'Look over here!' or 'Look over there!' Rather, the Father's kingdom is already spread out over the earth, and people don't see it."%0a%0a %0a%0aSaying 114: Peter and Mary%0a%0aSimon Peter said to them, "Mary should leave us, because women aren't worthy of life."%0a%0aJesus said, "Look, am I to make her a man? So that she may become a living spirit too, she's equal to you men, because every woman who makes herself manly will enter the kingdom of heaven."%0a%0a %0a%0aThe Gospel%0aAccording to Thomas%0a%0a %0a%0aNotes on Translation%0a%0aSaying 13: "Three things." Or possibly "three words." The Coptic term for "word" can also be translated as "saying," as in the incipit.%0a%0aSayings 16, 49, and 75: "One." Literally, monachos, usually translated "single," "solitary," or "alone." For the translation choice, cf. my book The Gospel of Thomas: A New Translation for Spiritual Seekers (CreateSpace Independent Publishing Platform), 2015, pp. 24,25, building on Cynthia Bourgeault, The Wisdom Jesus: Transforming Heart and Mind â€“ a New Perspective on Christ and His Message (Shambhala), 2009, p. 21; "The Gift of Life: The Unified Solitude of the Desert Fathers," Parabola, 1989, Vol. 14, No. 2, pp. 27,28; building in turn on Gabriele Winkler, "The Origins and Idiosyncrasies of the Earliest Form of Ascetisicm," The Continuing Quest for God: Monastic Spirituality in Tradition and Transition, ed. William Skuldarek, O.S.B. (The Liturgical Press), 1981, pp. 28,29.%0a%0aSaying 61: "Equal." The Coptic literally reads "destroyed," which may be a scribal error; if one letter is changed, the word would be "equal," which would echo the earlier phrase "I am the one who exists in equality."%0a%0aSaying 65: "Creditor." Or possibly "a good person"; cf. Michael W. Grondin, "Good Man or Usurer? Battle over a Lacuna," rev. May 31, 2014, on-line at http://gospel-thomas.net/lacuna.htm. Last accessed August 1, 2015.%0a%0aSaying 105: "A bastard." Literally, "the son of a prostitute."%0a%0aSaying 114: "Manly." Cf. my book The Gospel of Thomas, op. cit., pp. 25,26, building on Samuel Zinner, The Gospel of Thomas in the Light of Early Jewish, Christian and Islamic Esoteric Trajectories: with a contextualized commentary and a new translation of the Thomas Gospel (The Matheson Trust), 2011, pp. 288-290; building in turn on Paul SchÃ¼ngel, "Ein Vorschlag, EvTho 114 neu zu Ã¼bersetzen," Novum Testamentum, 1994, Vol. 36, No. 4, pp. 394-401.
