ning on having guests. When dinner was ready, they sent their servant to call the visitors.%0a%3c %0a%3c "The servant went to the first and said, 'My master invites you.'%0a%3c %0a%3c "They said, 'Some merchants owe me money. They're coming tonight. I need to go and give them instructions. Excuse me from the dinner.'%0a%3c %0a%3c "The servant went to another one and said, 'My master invites you.'%0a%3c %0a%3c "They said, "I've just bought a house and am needed for the day. I won't have time.'%0a%3c %0a%3c "The servant went to another one and said, 'My master invites you.'%0a%3c %0a%3c "They said, 'My friend is getting married and I'm going to make dinner. I can't come. Excuse me from the dinner.'%0a%3c %0a%3c "The servant went to another one and said, 'My master invites you.'%0a%3c %0a%3c "They said, "I've just bought a farm and am going to collect the rent. I can't come. Excuse me.'%0a%3c %0a%3c "The servant went back and told the master, 'The ones you've invited to the dinner have excused themselves.'%0a%3c %0a%3c "The master said to their servant, 'Go out to the roads and bring whomever you find so that they can have dinner.'%0a%3c %0a%3c "Buyers and merchants won't [enter] the places of my Father."%0a%3c %0a%3c  %0a%3c %0a%3c Saying 65: The Parable of the Sharecroppers%0a%3c %0a%3c He said, "A [creditor] owned a vineyard. He leased it out to some sharecroppers to work it so he could collect its fruit.%0a%3c %0a%3c "He sent his servant so that the sharecroppers could give him the fruit of the vineyard. They seized his servant, beat him, and nearly killed him.%0a%3c %0a%3c "The servant went back and told his master. His master said, 'Maybe he just didn't know them.' He sent another servant, but the tenants beat that one too.%0a%3c %0a%3c "Then the master sent his son, thinking, 'Maybe they'll show some respect to my son.'%0a%3c %0a%3c "Because they knew that he was the heir of the vineyard, the sharecroppers seized and killed him. Anyone who has ears to hear should hear!"%0a%3c %0a%3c  %0a%3c %0a%3c Saying 66: The Rejected Cornerstone%0a%3c %0a%3c Jesus said, "Show me the stone the builders rejected; that's the cornerstone."%0a%3c %0a%3c  %0a%3c %0a%3c Saying 67: Knowing Isn't Everything%0a%3c %0a%3c Jesus said, "Whoever knows everything, but is personally lacking, lacks everything."%0a%3c %0a%3c  %0a%3c %0a%3c Saying 68: Persecution%0a%3c %0a%3c Jesus said, "Blessed are you when you're hated and persecuted, and no place will be found where you've been persecuted."%0a%3c %0a%3c  %0a%3c %0a%3c Saying 69: Those Who Are Persecuted%0a%3c %0a%3c Jesus said, "Blessed are those who've been persecuted in their own hearts. They've truly known the Father. Blessed are those who are hungry, so that their stomachs may be filled."%0a%3c %0a%3c  %0a%3c %0a%3c Saying 70: Salvation is Within%0a%3c %0a%3c Jesus said, "If you give birth to what's within you, what you have within you will save you. If you don't have that within [you], what you don't have within you [will] kill you."%0a%3c %0a%3c  %0a%3c %0a%3c Saying 71: Destroying the Temple%0a%3c %0a%3c Jesus said, "I'll destroy [this] house, and no one will be able to build it [â€¦]"%0a%3c %0a%3c  %0a%3c %0a%3c Saying 72: Not a Divider%0a%3c %0a%3c [Someone said to him], "Tell my brothers to divide our inheritance with me."%0a%3c %0a%3c He said to him, "Who made me a divider?"%0a%3c %0a%3c He turned to his disciples and said to them, "Am I really a divider?"%0a%3c %0a%3c  %0a%3c %0a%3c Saying 73: Workers for the Harvest%0a%3c %0a%3c Jesus said, "The harvest really is plentiful, but the workers are few. So pray that the Lord will send workers to the harvest."%0a%3c %0a%3c  %0a%3c %0a%3c Saying 74: The Empty Well%0a%3c %0a%3c He said, "Lord, many are gathered around the well, but there's nothing to drink."%0a%3c %0a%3c  %0a%3c %0a%3c Saying 75: The Bridal Chamber%0a%3c %0a%3c Jesus said, "Many are waiting at the door, but those who are one will enter the bridal chamber."%0a%3c %0a%3c  %0a%3c %0a%3c Saying 76: The Parable of the Pearl%0a%3c %0a%3c Jesus said, "The Father's kingdom can be compared to a merchant with merchandise who found a pearl. The merchant was wise; they sold their merchandise and bought that single pearl for themselves.%0a%3c %0a%3c "You, too, look for the treasure that doesn't perish but endures, where no moths come to eat and no worms destroy."%0a%3c %0a%3c  %0a%3c %0a%3c Saying 77: Jesus is the All%0a%3c %0a%3c Jesus said, "I'm the light that's over all. I am the All. The All has come from me and unfolds toward me.%0a%3c %0a%3c "Split a log; I'm there. Lift the stone, and you'll find me there."%0a%3c %0a%3c  %0a%3c %0a%3c Saying 78: Into the Desert%0a%3c %0a%3c Jesus said, "What did you go out into the desert to see? A reed shaken by the wind? A [person] wearing fancy clothes, [like your] rulers and powerful people? They (wear) fancy [clothes], but can't know the truth."%0a%3c %0a%3c  %0a%3c %0a%3c Saying 79: Listening to the Message%0a%3c %0a%3c A woman in the crowd said to him, "Blessed is the womb that bore you, and the breasts that nourished you."%0a%3c %0a%3c He said to [her], "Blessed are those who have listened to the message of the Father and kept it, because there will be days when you'll say, 'Blessed is the womb that didn't conceive and the breasts that haven't given milk.'"%0a%3c %0a%3c  %0a%3c %0a%3c Saying 80: The World is a Body%0a%3c %0a%3c Jesus said, "Whoever has known the world has found the body; but whoever has found the body, of them the world isn't worthy."%0a%3c %0a%3c  %0a%3c %0a%3c Saying 81: Riches and Renunciation (1)%0a%3c %0a%3c Jesus said, "Whoever has become rich should become a ruler, and whoever has power should renounce it."%0a%3c %0a%3c  %0a%3c %0a%3c Saying 82: Jesus and Fire (2)%0a%3c %0a%3c Jesus said, "Whoever is near me is near the fire, and whoever is far from me is far from the kingdom."%0a%3c %0a%3c  %0a%3c %0a%3c Saying 83: Light and Images%0a%3c %0a%3c Jesus said, "Images are revealed to